You are working on jianlai.wiki, a Nuxt + Nuxt Content fandom encyclopedia for Jian Lai / Sword, Come!.

Use UI UX Pro Max principles if available.

Design direction:
- modern cinematic Shuimo / 水墨
- black-white ink-wash identity
- premium fandom wiki
- restrained red seal accents
- official donghua-inspired atmosphere
- media-rich but readable
- animated but not flashy

Avoid:
- documentation-like layouts
- Nuxt starter feel
- SaaS/dashboard cards
- generic wiki styling
- flat static pages
- heavy colorful gradients
- overusing borders
- overusing official assets

Technical constraints:
- Keep Nuxt + Nuxt Content
- Static generation only
- No backend
- No database
- No authentication
- No heavy dependencies
- Do not break existing routes
- Do not delete existing content
- Run npm run generate after major changes

Media rules:
- Do not use public/videos/all-mp4 directly
- Use only curated videos in public/videos/curated
- Keep public/images/official as raw archive/reference
- Use curated assets in public/images/banners, textures, characters, ui
- Add credit/caption support for official media

Testing rules:
- Use http://localhost:3000/ for browser testing
- Do not rely on random preview ports
- Check desktop and mobile when possible